  "title": "free walking study",
  "description": "A mobile EEG study examining gait-related artifacts during naturalistic walking behavior. Nineteen participants completed outdoor walking tasks along two different routes, with repeated trials including a self-paced button-pressing condition. This dataset provides insights into the challenges of acquiring high-quality EEG recordings in real-world, ambulatory settings.",
  "methods_description": "Mobile EEG recordings were collected from 19 participants during free walking outdoors. Subjects walked two different routes, each traversed twice—once during normal walking and once while performing self-paced button presses. Detailed methodological information is provided in the associated publication.",
